headline.main: FOUR DAYS LATER FROM EUROPE; The U. S. Sloop-of-War Portsmouth at Bangkok. LORD ELGIN'S INTENDED POLICY. Mr. Macaulay Elevated to the British Peerage. Cotton and Breadstuffs Dull---Consols 90 3-4. ARRIVAL OF THE BALTIC. INTERESTING FROM CHINA. The Terrible Massacre at Cawnpore. Further Details of the Indian Mutinies, Position of the Besiegers at Delhi

docs.lead_paragraph: The United States Mail steamship Baltic, Capt. COMSTOCK, which sailed from Liverpool about 10 o'clock on the morning of Wednesday, Sept. 2, arrived here at 9 o'clock yesterday morning, bringing 135 passengers.
